Reasoning: The paper deals with the characterization of non-line-of-sight (NLOS) bias error in range measurements, which is a common problem in wireless communication systems. The paper uses tools from stochastic geometry to provide the first analytical backing for an NLOS bias error model. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Machine Learning (cs.MA), and Multimedia (cs.MM).
